item.title: Google -- Thank you for giving us Tensorflow and Keras...
item.description: First what is Deep Learning? Deep Learning. What? Ok I confess. I know how to implement some of these deep(er) learning algorithms, but I’m just now getting my brain around how they work. And as caveat. I’m focused driven. My thinking is if I test my model on new data (data the model hasn’t seen) many times over and get good results, what the heck do I care how the thing works under the hood?
